#  CRUD Operations using Node.js, Express.js & MongoDB

##  Project Overview
This project demonstrates how to perform **CRUD Operations (Create, Read, Update, Delete)** using a **Node.js and Express.js backend** with **MongoDB** as the database.

It is a RESTful API-based application where users can manage student records efficiently.

---

##  Objective
- Build REST APIs using Node.js and Express.js
- Connect backend with MongoDB database
- Perform CRUD operations
- Test APIs using Postman
- Understand routing and backend architecture

---

##  Features
-  Create new student records
-  Fetch all students
-  Fetch single student by ID
-  Update student details
-  Delete student record

---

##  Tech Stack
- Node.js
- Express.js
- MongoDB
- Mongoose
- Postman

---

##  Project Structure
experiment10/
├── server.js
├── models/
│   └── Student.js
├── routes/
│   └── studentRoutes.js
├── package.json

---

##  Installation & Setup

###  Clone or Create Project
bash
mkdir experiment10
cd experiment10
npm init -y

brew services start mongodb-community

node server.js

http://localhost:5000